# Task 1: Introduction — Linux Strength Training (TryHackMe)

Welcome to my walkthrough of the **Linux Strength Training** room on [TryHackMe]. This task serves as the **starting point** for anyone looking to improve their Linux command line skills.

## Objectives of This Task

- Practice **basic Linux commands**
- Build analytical thinking for solving CLI-based challenges
- Get prepared for deeper tasks by completing these prerequisite rooms first:
  - [Learn Linux Part 1](https://tryhackme.com/room/zlinux)
  - [Learn Linux Part 2](https://tryhackme.com/room/zlinuxpart2)
  - [Learn Linux Part 3](https://tryhackme.com/room/zlinuxpart3)


## Key Takeaways

Although no technical commands are required in this task, you should understand:

- This room will walk you through practical Linux scenarios.
- You’ll need to use tools like `find`, `grep`, `gpg`, `john`, `sqlite3`, and more.
- Challenges build up your knowledge gradually — ideal for beginners!


## Task Summary

In this repository, each task will have its own directory with:
- Notes and explanations
- Commands used
- Answers to TryHackMe questions (when applicable)

You can follow along with this repo to reinforce your own Linux CLI training.


## Ready to Start?

Move on to [Task 2: Finding Your Way Around Linux](../Task-2_Finding-Files/README.md)
